Nano test.txt

opens immediately a file called test.txt ready to take notes

If you just type

nano

then it will open a temporary file (to take quick notes is even faster than the previous command)



copy and paste with Nano

first press

ctrl+6

this will set mar
then move with arrows to select text

now to copy

alt + 6

to paste
ctrl+u


____________________

move with nano at the end of the file:

ctrl+w and then ctrl+v
